(URL Shortener Project Explanation) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(What This Project Does) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This project is a Laravel and React based URL shortener.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The main purpose is simple:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. A user enters a long URL.) Tj
T*
(2. The app generates a short random code.) Tj
T*
(3. The app creates a short link.) Tj
T*
(4. When someone opens the short link, the app redirects them to the original long URL.) Tj
T*
(5. The app records click analytics in the background.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Example:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Long URL:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```txt) Tj
T*
(https://example.com/some/very/long/url/with/query/params) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Short URL:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```txt) Tj
T*
(https://yourdomain.com/J7qudkrM) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(What To Say About The Project) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This is a full-stack URL shortener application built with Laravel for the backend and React) Tj
T*
(for the frontend.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The user can paste a long URL, click the shorten button, and the system generates a short) Tj
T*
(8-character link. When that short link is opened, Laravel finds the original URL in the) Tj
T*
(database and redirects the user to it.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The project also tracks clicks using a queue-based system so that redirects stay fast even) Tj
T*
(when many users are clicking links.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why Local Links Show 127.0.0.1 Or 8001) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(During development, the Laravel server runs locally on the computer.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(That is why links may look like:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```txt) Tj
T*
(http://127.0.0.1:8001/J7qudkrM) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Here:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- `127.0.0.1` means the local computer.) Tj
T*
(- `8001` is the local Laravel development server port.) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
