T*
(This is normal during local development.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(What Happens After Hosting) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(After buying a domain and hosting the project publicly, the link will not show `127.0.0.1`) Tj
T*
(or `8001`.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(It will look like:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```txt) Tj
T*
(https://yourdomain.com/J7qudkrM) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(or with a short domain:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```txt) Tj
T*
(https://lnksrt.in/J7qudkrM) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Public HTTPS websites use port `443`, and browsers hide that port automatically.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(So users will only see the clean domain and short code.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Can The Domain Be Removed Completely?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(No, a public URL cannot work without a domain.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This will not work properly:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```txt) Tj
T*
(http://J7qudkrM) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Because the browser will think `J7qudkrM` is the domain name.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(A real short link must have:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```txt) Tj
T*
(https://domain.com/code) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Example:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```txt) Tj
T*
(https://lnksrt.in/J7qudkrM) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Will Local Links Work On Mobile?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(A local link like this will not work on mobile:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```txt) Tj
T*
