(Why Queue Is Used) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Click tracking is done using a queue.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This keeps redirects fast.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Instead of making the user wait while analytics are saved, the app redirects immediately and) Tj
T*
(records analytics in the background.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(For local development, the project can use the database queue.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(For production, Redis can be used for better performance.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Redis And Kafka) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Redis is used for:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Faster cache) Tj
T*
(- Faster queue processing) Tj
T*
(- Better performance when many users are clicking links) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Kafka-style event publishing is included as a clean architecture layer.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Right now, click events are logged.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Later, a real Kafka producer can be connected if the project needs event streaming at large) Tj
T*
(scale.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
